Subject: RE: Netwrix Support Ticket #442858 -  - Jobs fails post upgrade from 11.6.0.141 to 12.0.0.153    [ ref:!00D70091pB.!500Qk0OLq94:ref ]

TextBody:
Hello Matthew,

Please cancel the FileSystem0.Collection0-Create Schema job, navigate to SQL Server Management Studio and run these commands:
 

ALTER TABLE SA_FSAA_ResourcesScanTypeDetails NOCHECK CONSTRAINT ALL;
ALTER TABLE SA_FSAA_ResourceMap NOCHECK CONSTRAINT ALL;

Re-run the FileSystem0.Collection0-Create Schema job. Once completed, navigate back to SQL Server Management Studio and run these commands:
 

ALTER TABLE SA_FSAA_ResourcesScanTypeDetails WITH CHECK CHECK CONSTRAINT ALL;
ALTER TABLE SA_FSAA_ResourceMap WITH CHECK CHECK CONSTRAINT ALL;
Please share your findings afterwards.

Have a great day!

Saqib Sharif
Technical Support Engineer

Please cancel the FileSystem0.Collection0-Create Schema job, navigate to SQL Server Management Studio and run these commands:

Re-run the FileSystem0.Collection0-Create Schema job. Once completed, navigate back to SQL Server Management Studio and run these commands:




ALTER TABLE SA_FSAA_ResourcesScanTypeDetails WITH CHECK CHECK CONSTRAINT ALL;

ALTER TABLE SA_FSAA_ResourceMap WITH CHECK CHECK CONSTRAINT ALL;
Please share your findings afterwards.

TextBody:
Hello Matthew,

Thank you for taking the time to meet today.

Today we:
checked the error that was popping when running the Create-Schema job. To resolve that issue, we opened SQL Server Management Studio and identified the full path to DB tables to be used. We modified the commands as follows:
 

ALTER TABLE [DB_NAME].[dbo].[SA_FSAA_ResourcesScanTypeDetails] NOCHECK CONSTRAINT ALL;
ALTER TABLE [DB_NAME].[dbo].[SA_FSAA_ResourceMap] NOCHECK CONSTRAINT ALL;

Similarly, the other set of SQL queries was also modified to:
 

ALTER TABLE [DB_NAME].[dbo].[SA_FSAA_ResourcesScanTypeDetails] WITH CHECK CHECK CONSTRAINT ALL;
ALTER TABLE [DB_NAME].[dbo].[SA_FSAA_ResourceMap] WITH CHECK CHECK CONSTRAINT ALL;

The first set of commands was run but there was already a scheduled job running and it was taking very long.

Our next steps are:
You will:
Since there was a scheduled job running, it was decided that you will run the first set of commands, execute the create schema job.


To go through the process tomorrow once the scheduled jobs complete, please use this link to schedule our next meeting at your convenience:

nwxcorp.my.salesforce-sites.com/cts?Id=bIBPlm5g_GBdFLAlVFl8wQtdfs9cnT9GSOGAQfFJaEY-Z&MeetingID=hR0xZ7zfxFB_RolUkj66V7BZ1gnfpb7Xr8BR1caZ0AE-Z
